(338, '180-5057', 'View O2 Pulse Oximeter with Case', 'view-o2-pulse-oximeter-with-case', 0, 0, 0, 431, '<ul><li>Portable, non-invasive monitoring device</li><li>Exclusive "high definition" OLED color screen</li><li>Multi - directional readout with 4 display modes</li><li>10 brightness settings</li><li>Accommodates most finger sizes (pediatric to adult)</li><li>Includes FREE shock guard, neck lanyard and 2 AAA batteries with purchase</li><li>Auto-off after 8 seconds of non-use preserves battery life </li><li>No calibration required</li><li>Low battery indicator</li><li>FDA compliant</li><li>No prescription required </li><li>2 year warranty</li></ul>', '', '', 0.00, 0.00, '', 33.80, 33.80, '0000-00-00', '0000-00-00', 0, 1, 1, 0, '0', 0, 9998, '', '{"d57f3711ae86931":{"filename":"d57f3711ae86931.png","alt":"","caption":"","primary":true},"dfecfc4ff16af03":{"filename":"dfecfc4ff16af03.png","alt":"","caption":""}}', 'View O2 Pulse Oximeter with Case', '', 0, '<p><strong>My unit won’t read the SPO2 or pulse rate or the reading is unstable.</strong><br>Remove finger and reinsert, ensure it is placed properly over sensor.  Ensure patient is not moving.  Remove fingernail polish if present.</p><p><strong>My unit won’t power on.</strong><br>Verify correct battery installation.  Replace batteries.</p><p><strong>My screen turns off.</strong><br>This device automatically powers off after 8 seconds of inactivity to conserver batter life.  Battery may also have low power, replace batteries.</p><p><strong>I get an Error3, Error4 or Error7 message.</strong><br>Unit may have low power, replace the batteries.  If this does not fix the problem, a sensor or circuit may be blocked or damage, contact customer service for warranty evaluation.</p>', '<p><strong>Measurement Ranges</strong></p><ul><li>Oxygen Saturation: 70 - 99%</li><li>Pulse Rate: 30 - 235 bpm</li><li>SPO2 Accuracty: +/- 3% 70 - 99%</li></ul><p>For pediatric use – minimum 20 lbs and 1 year</p><p>Operating temperature: 40-10